SIMPLE: practicer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Practicer
<hw>Prac"ti*cer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Often written
<ets>practiser</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who practices, or puts
in practice; one who customarily performs certain acts.</def>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who exercises a profession; a
practitioner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who uses art or stratagem.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Practician</ent>⟦br⟧
